{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PLAN-REVIEW REMEDIATION (Round-11, 2026-06-29) — disposition summary (full resolutions in the epic '## Round-11 remediation' section; derisk evidence in session_log a7e2-381c-6dc6-4d0c EXPERIMENT 2).\n\nRESOLVED in Round-11 section + child edits: adapter-seam contradiction (now code_review_decision(diff_text, repo_root, ref)→{decision}, named module, co-located fail-closed rule, covering AC on S4b); webhook-carries-no-diff (PROVEN; S4b base64-decode AC); outbound read credential (bot HTTP token doubles as REST + git-over-HTTPS read; S1 scaffolds, S4a provisions); SSM alert-endpoint + bot-token scaffolding (S1); EC2-role / gerrit.config / DLM ownership contracts; BSL citation (S5 ADR-0010); events-log backfill smoke-check (S4a); plan-before-apply discipline (epic-level + S7 runbook).\n\nALREADY-ADDRESSED (kept, with justification — not silently ignored):\n- S6-pre snapshot FORM (T4 major): dcea already specifies a machine-readable JSON ruleset export ( via gh api, 'sufficient to recreate on rollback') — the finding's concern is already met; no change needed.\n- copyCondition NO_CODE_CHANGE empirical validation (T2/T3 major): S3 (a88d) AC3 already requires verifying BOTH directions on live 3.14.1 (message-only amend carries the vote; a real rebase drops it). That IS the empirical probe the finding asks for; reaffirmed.\n- Rollback drill / freeze-restore (T12 major): S7 already has a restore drill on a throwaway instance (≤2h RTO) and S6 a <15-min ruleset rollback from the S6-pre snapshot; the 'drill' concern is covered by S7's restore-drill AC. Reaffirmed; the ruleset-rollback rehearsal is folded into S6's documented <15-min procedure.\n- Monitoring metrics/alarms undefined (T10 major): S7 already defines a concrete custom metric (Rebar/Gate/GerritReachable), the alarm (<1 for 2 periods, treat_missing_data=breaching), the EC2 StatusCheckFailed backstop, and SNS→SSM endpoint. The finding's 'no concrete metrics/alarms' reads against the lean epic body, but the child S7 ACs specify them; reaffirmed.\n- gerrit config DRIFT management (T10 major): addressed by the gerrit.config ownership contract (S2 base + S3 [change]-only RMW) + infra-as-code under infra/; configs are rendered/committed, not hand-edited, so terraform/compose is the drift source of truth."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782766571948955001,"uuid":"668b8967-1140-4f7a-b451-203275af459c"}